snippet.textDisplay:
We fans just like to play the blame game don’t we. Yeah the board at Manchester United have been a shambles no body is arguing with that.
I do not blame them for Haaland going to Dortmund. What’s the point of signing a young kid who’s got the potential to be worth £150m in a few years and then agreeing to insert a release clause of £51 million that Riola wanted. It’s time to stop giving in to these agents. No big club have a good relationship with Riola. There is a reason Barcelona worked away from De Ligt deal. I don’t believe £5mill is the reason holding up Bruno’s deal I believe it has something to do with Medes another super agent. That deal was going smoothly until he enters into the negotiation. We can’t be bending over for these super agents has Pogba’s situation thought no body any lesson.
Chong and Gomes contract have nothing to do with money. It’s play time that they’re worried about. Gomes will sign a contract he’s just nursing an injury at the moment.
